name: Asparagus
description: Asparagus is the tender young shoots of the species Asparagus officinalis, eaten, lightly cooked, as a vegetable. They shoots are called ‘spears’ and can be green, white or purple in colour.

name: Carrots
description: The carrot is a root vegetable, typically orange in color, though purple, red all of which are domesticated forms of the wild carrot Southwestern Asia.

name: Eggs
description: Eggs are laid by female animals of many different species and many of these have been eaten by humans for thousands of years

name: Flour
description: Flour is a powder made by grinding raw grains, roots, beans, nuts, or seeds. Flours are used to make many different foods.

name: Pulses
description: A legume is a plant in the family Fabaceae, or the fruit or seed of such a plant. When used as a dry grain, the seed is also called a pulse

name: Rice
description: Rice is the seed of the grass species Oryza sativa or less commonly Oryza glaberrima. The name wild rice is usually used for species
